    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Where are Kamtec products manufactured?",
            "answer": "<p>Kamtec GmbH is a <strong>German company</strong> headquartered in Metzingen, Baden-Wurttemberg. The brand was founded in Germany with a specialisation in circular saw blades and has since expanded to offer a comprehensive range of power tool accessories, protective gloves and telescopic ladders \u2014 all engineered to German quality standards.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Click 'n' Climb ladders safe for professional use?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Click 'n' Climb telescopic extension ladders are <strong>EN 131 compliant</strong>, meeting European safety standards for professional use. The patented soft-close mechanism retracts each rung individually and gently, preventing finger traps. Available in 2.9m and 3.8m extended heights with a maximum load rating suitable for trade use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What cutting discs does Kamtec offer?",
            "answer": "<p>Kamtec offers a comprehensive range of <strong>abrasive cutting discs</strong> for metal and stone, <strong>diamond blades</strong> for concrete and masonry, and <strong>circular saw blades</strong> for timber and sheet materials. All products are engineered to German standards for consistent performance and long service life.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Kamtec protective gloves EN-rated?",
            "answer": "<p>Kamtec offers a comprehensive range of protective gloves that carry appropriate <strong>EN ratings</strong> for mechanical risks including cut resistance, abrasion, tear and puncture. The range covers everything from heavy-duty construction gloves to precision-grip assembly gloves, suitable for every industry and application.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How compact are Click 'n' Climb ladders for van storage?",
            "answer": "<p>Click 'n' Climb telescopic ladders collapse to a <strong>compact transport size</strong> that fits easily in a van, car boot or on a roof rack. The 2.9m ladder and 3.8m ladder both retract to a fraction of their extended height, making them ideal for tradespeople who need access equipment without sacrificing van space.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Kamtec products?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Kamtec range including cutting accessories, ladders and protective gloves. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
